# ============================================================================
# TRIVY IGNORE FILE
# auto-code-scanning
#
# This file contains suppressions for Trivy security scanner findings.
# All entries MUST have documented justifications.
#
# Trivy runs LOCALLY - no code is uploaded to external services.
#
# FORMATS:
#   AVD-ID                           # Suppress by ID globally
#   path/to/file AVD-ID              # Suppress by ID in specific file
#   path/to/file:line AVD-ID         # Suppress by ID at specific line
#
# FINDING IDs:
#   AVD-AWS-*                        # AWS misconfigurations
#   AVD-GCP-*                        # GCP misconfigurations
#   CVE-*                            # Known vulnerabilities
#
# Manual run:
#   trivy config . --ignorefile .trivyignore
#
# Documentation:
#   https://aquasecurity.github.io/trivy/latest/docs/configuration/filtering/
# ============================================================================

# ============================================================================
# GLOBAL SUPPRESSIONS
# These apply to all files in the repository
# ============================================================================

# Example: Suppress a specific check globally
# AVD-AWS-0057  # Reason: S3 lifecycle rules managed at composition layer

# ============================================================================
# FILE-SPECIFIC SUPPRESSIONS
# Format: path/to/file AVD-ID  # Reason
# ============================================================================

# Example: Suppress in specific module
# terraform/modules/s3/main.tf AVD-AWS-0089  # Reason: Bucket policy handled separately

# ============================================================================
# LINE-SPECIFIC SUPPRESSIONS
# Format: path/to/file:line AVD-ID  # Reason
# ============================================================================

# Example: Suppress at specific line
# terraform/modules/vpc/main.tf:45 AVD-AWS-0101  # Reason: VPC flow logs in separate module

# ============================================================================
# NOTES
# ============================================================================
#
# 1. Always document WHY a finding is being suppressed
# 2. Review suppressions quarterly to see if they're still needed
# 3. Prefer fixing issues over suppressing them
# 4. For false positives, consider reporting to Trivy project
#
# To find finding IDs, run:
#   trivy config . --severity CRITICAL,HIGH,MEDIUM --format json
#
# ============================================================================
